			<div id="post-3837" class="post-3837 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-breakfast-brunch category-dessert category-drink category-entree category-food tag-banana tag-cinnamon tag-frozen tag-healthy tag-ice tag-oatmeal-raisin-cookie tag-oatmeal-raisin-cookie-smoothie tag-old-fashioned-oats tag-quick-cooking-oats tag-raisins tag-skim-milk tag-smoothie tag-vanilla-whey-protein-powder">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/04/oatmeal-raisin-cookie-smoothie" title="Permalink to Oatmeal Raisin Cookie {Smoothie}" rel="bookmark">Oatmeal Raisin Cookie {Smoothie}</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/04/oatmeal-raisin-cookie-smoothie" title="6:55 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">April 6, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/author/caroline" title="View all posts by caroline">caroline</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Oatmeal-Raisin-Cookie-Smoothie-0119.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3839" title="Oatmeal Raisin Cookie Smoothie-0119" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Oatmeal-Raisin-Cookie-Smoothie-0119.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Nothing is more <strong>devine</strong> that a smoothie that tastes like a <strong>cookie</strong>.</p>
<p>And now that summer is fast approaching, you&#8217;ll need a cool treat to satisfy both your sweet tooth and thirst!</p>
<p>Give it a try&#8230;you won&#8217;t be sorry!</p>
<h6>P.S. It was 80°F when I made these and once I took them outside and got my camera out, they were already starting to melt. So they might not look too pretty, but they sure to taste good! <img src='http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif' alt=':-D' class='wp-smiley' /> </h6>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Oatmeal-Raisin-Cookie-Smoothie-0119.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Oatmeal-Raisin-Cookie-Smoothie-0127.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3840" title="Oatmeal Raisin Cookie Smoothie-0127" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Oatmeal-Raisin-Cookie-Smoothie-0127.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="372" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Oatmeal Raisin Cookie {Smoothie}</strong></p>
<p><em>Ingredients</em></p>
<ul>
<li>2 medium bananas</li>
<li>2 scoops of vanilla whey protein powder</li>
<li>1/3 cup old fashioned or quick cooking oats</li>
<li>1/2 tablespoon cinnamon</li>
<li>1 tablespoon raisins</li>
<li>2/3 cup skim milk</li>
<li>1 cup crushed ice</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To</em></p>
<ol>
<li>Blend together and enjoy!</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Servings: 2-4 (It&#8217;s a meal for 2 or a snack for 4)</em></p>
<p><em><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/nutrition.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3843" title="nutrition" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/nutrition.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" /></a><br />
</em></p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
