			<div id="post-3794" class="post-3794 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-chocolate category-cookie category-dessert category-food tag-banana tag-cane-syrup tag-cashews tag-chocolate-sauce tag-cookie-dough tag-dark-chocolate-chips tag-frozen tag-homemade tag-natural-cane-sugar tag-old-fashioned-oats tag-skim-milk tag-soft-serve tag-vanilla-extract tag-whole-wheat-flour">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/04/homemade-cookie-dough-soft-serve" title="Permalink to {Homemade} Cookie Dough Soft Serve" rel="bookmark">{Homemade} Cookie Dough Soft Serve</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/04/homemade-cookie-dough-soft-serve" title="6:18 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">April 4, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/author/caroline" title="View all posts by caroline">caroline</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-9770.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3797" title="Cookie Dough Softserve-9770" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-9770.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="369" /></a></p>
<p>So, as you may very well know by now, I&#8217;m not only a chocoholic, but I LOVE ice cream/frozen yogurt/soft serve.</p>
<p>In fact, when Logan and were first dating. I think I literally gained about 20 pounds in one summer because we got ice cream so much! <em>Especially the Ultimate Brownie Sundae from Kaminsky&#8217;s in Charleston. </em>Yum!!!<em><br />
</em></p>
<p><em><br />
</em></p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-9770.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-9768.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3796" title="Cookie Dough Softserve-9768" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-9768.jpg" alt="" width="349" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>Anyway. If you&#8217;re as crazy about frozen treats as me, you&#8217;ll love this dessert.</p>
<p>And there&#8217;s no ice cream involved!</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-Small.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3795" title="Cookie Dough Softserve Small" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Cookie-Dough-Softserve-Small.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Homemade Cookie Dough Soft Serve</strong></p>
<h6><em>from <a href="http://ohsheglows.com/2011/03/18/chocolate-chip-cooke-dough-blizzard/" target="_blank">Oh She Glows</a></em></h6>
<p><em>Ingredients (Cookie Dough)<br />
</em></p>
<ul>
<li>1/2 cup lightly salted cashews</li>
<li>1/4 cup old fashioned oats</li>
<li>1/4 cup whole wheat flour</li>
<li>1.5 tablespoons natural cane sugar</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract</li>
<li>3 tablespoons natural cane syrup <em>(I used Log Cabin)</em></li>
<li>1/4 cup 60% cacao dark chocolate chips (or your favorite chocolate chip)</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To (Cookie Dough)<br />
</em></p>
<ol>
<li>In a food processor, grind the cashews and oats until it looks like flour.</li>
<li>Add in the flour and sugar and quickly grind again to combine.</li>
<li>Add in the vanilla and syrup and blend until the dough is of a moldable consistency (you may have to add some more syrup if it is too dry).</li>
<li>Stir in the chocolate chips.</li>
<li>Roll the dough out into tablespoon-sized balls and place them on a plate.</li>
<li>Freeze the cookie dough balls.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Ingredients (Soft Serve)</em></p>
<ul>
<li>5 peeled and frozen bananas</li>
<li>1/4 cup skim milk</li>
<li>6 frozen cookie dough balls</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To (Soft Serve)<br />
</em></p>
<ol>
<li>In a large food processor, blend all of the ingredients until it is a smooth consistency.</li>
<li>Top with a couple of cookie dough balls.</li>
<li>Drizzle the top with dark chocolate syrup and enjoy!</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Servings: 3-4</em></p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
