			<div id="post-3753" class="post-3753 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-chicken-turkey category-entree category-food tag-black-pepper tag-breadcrumbs tag-dinner tag-easy tag-fast tag-ground-turkey tag-healthy tag-italian-seasoning tag-marinara-sauce tag-part-skim-mozzarella-cheese tag-portabella-mushroom">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/turkey-stuffed-portabella-mushrooms" title="Permalink to Turkey Stuffed Portabella Mushrooms" rel="bookmark">Turkey Stuffed Portabella Mushrooms</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/turkey-stuffed-portabella-mushrooms" title="1:55 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">March 31, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/author/caroline" title="View all posts by caroline">caroline</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9584.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3754" title="Turkey Meatball stuffed Portabellas-9584" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9584.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>Looks tasty, eh?</p>
<p>I practically made this in under 5 minutes.</p>
<p>And if you ask me, this is the perfect solution to a quick &amp; healthy weekday meal! <img src='http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif' alt=':-D' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>&#8230;and I forgot to mention super tasty!!!</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9591.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3755" title="Turkey Meatball stuffed Portabellas-9591" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9591.jpg" alt="" width="332" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>There ya go&#8230;an action shot of extra Parmesan cheese. <img src='http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif' alt=':-D' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9606.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3756" title="Turkey Meatball stuffed Portabellas-9606" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9606.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>This meal was super filling (see nutrition facts below&#8230;look at all of that protein in one Turkey Stuffed Portabella!) and for only 373 calories. It&#8217;s the perfect guilt free way to enjoy some Italian flavors. Mmm!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9616.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3757" title="Turkey Meatball stuffed Portabellas-9616" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Turkey-Meatball-stuffed-Portabellas-9616.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="474" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>And yes, Logan and I both cleaned out plates.</p>
<p>Then let Leland make them clean enough to go back on the shelves.</p>
<p> <img src='http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt=';-)' class='wp-smiley' />  Just kidding&#8230;don&#8217;t worry, they went through the dishwasher too&#8230;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Screen-shot-2011-03-31-at-2.48.57-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3758" title="Screen shot 2011-03-31 at 2.48.57 PM" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Screen-shot-2011-03-31-at-2.48.57-PM.png" alt="" width="269" height="543" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Turkey Stuffed Portabella Mushrooms</strong></p>
<p><em>Ingredients</em></p>
<ul>
<li>1/2 pound ground lean turkey</li>
<li>1 tablespoon breadcrumbs</li>
<li>1 tablespoon Perfect Pinch Italian seasoning (or you could just use Italian breadcrumbs that have these spices in them all ready)</li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon fresh ground black pepper</li>
<li>1 cup of your favorite marinara sauce</li>
<li>2 large portabella mushrooms</li>
<li>1 cup shredded part skim mozzarella cheese</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To</em></p>
<ol>
<li>In a oven safe dish, spread the marinara sauce out on the bottom.</li>
<li>Prepare the mushrooms by washing and taking out the stem. Set aside.</li>
<li>In a bowl, combine the turkey, breadcrumbs, seasoning and pepper.</li>
<li>Divide and shape the turkey mixture into two even patties.</li>
<li>Press the patties down in the portabella mushroom.</li>
<li>Place the stuffed mushrooms down on the marinara sauce.</li>
<li>Bake for 30 minutes.</li>
<li>Sprinkle the cheese on top of the stuffed mushrooms and bake about another 15-20 minutes until the meat is completely cooked through.</li>
<li>At this point I broiled the dish on high for just a minute or so to brown the cheese a little bit.</li>
<li>Serve and enjoy!</li>
</ol>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
