			<div id="post-3567" class="post-3567 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-cookie category-dessert category-food tag-birthday tag-cane-sugar tag-egg tag-meringue-powder tag-powdered-sugar tag-royal-icing tag-salt tag-star-wars tag-sugar-cookie tag-unbleached-all-purpose-flour tag-unsalted-butter tag-vanilla-extract tag-water">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/star-wars-cookies" title="Permalink to Star Wars Cookies" rel="bookmark">Star Wars Cookies</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/star-wars-cookies" title="6:16 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">March 25, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/author/caroline" title="View all posts by caroline">caroline</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/StarWarsWar.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3687" title="StarWarsWar" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/StarWarsWar.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #0000ff;">Happy Birthday to my husband, Logan!</span></strong></h2>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/StarWarsWar.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Star-Wars-Cookies-6579.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3685" title="Star Wars Cookies-6579" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Star-Wars-Cookies-6579.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>This post is in honor of my dear husband who is a Star Wars freak. Anyone else have one of those in their family?</p>
<p>For Christmas I got the Star Wars cookie cutters from Williams-Sonoma. Excitement!!!</p>
<p>This is just a basic sugar cookie and icing recipe. Enjoy!</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Star-Wars-Cookies-6579.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Star-Wars-Cookies-6582.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3686" title="Star Wars Cookies-6582" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Star-Wars-Cookies-6582.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Sugar Cookies</strong></p>
<h6><strong> </strong><em>from Star Wars cookies by Williams Sonoma</em><strong><br />
</strong></h6>
<p><em>Ingredients</em></p>
<ul>
<li>2 1/2 cups unbleached all-purpose flour</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
<li>1 1/2 sticks unsalted butter, room temperature</li>
<li>1 cup cane sugar</li>
<li>1 egg, room temperature</li>
<li>1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To</em></p>
<ol>
<li>In a bowl, sift the flour and salt together and set aside.</li>
<li>In the bowl of your stand mixer, beat the butter on high speed until creamy (about 2 minutes).</li>
<li>Reduce the speed to medium and slowly add the sugar and beat until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes). <em>Don&#8217;t forget to scrape the bowl if necessary.</em></li>
<li>Add the egg and vanilla and beat for 1 minute.</li>
<li>Add half the flour mixture and beat on low speed until the flour has been absorbed (about 1 minute).</li>
<li>Add the remaining flour and beat until the flour has been absorbed and the dough starts to pull away from the sides of the bowl (about 2-3 minutes).</li>
<li>Turn the dough onto a long piece of plastic wrap and mold into a disk.</li>
<li>Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.</li>
<li>Remove the dough from the fridge, let it stand for 5 minutes and then roll it out onto a floured surface.</li>
<li>Roll out to about 1/4&#8243; &#8211; 1/2&#8243;.</li>
<li>Cut into desired shapes.</li>
<li>Bake for about 10-15 minutes in a 350° oven.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Royal Icing</strong></p>
<h6><strong> </strong><em>from <a href="http://www.wilton.com/recipe/Royal-Icing" target="_blank">Wilton</a></em></h6>
<p><em>Ingredients</em></p>
<ul>
<li>3 tablespoons Meringue Powder</li>
<li>1 pound of powdered sugar</li>
<li>4-6 tablespoons warm water</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To</em></p>
<ol>
<li>Beat ingredients together until it&#8217;s at the desired consistency.</li>
<li>Pipe cookies!</li>
</ol>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
