			<div id="post-3400" class="post-3400 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-dessert category-food category-pie-cobbler tag-bourbon tag-chocolate-chip-cookie-dough-pie tag-egg tag-peanuts tag-pie tag-reeses-peanut-butter-cups tag-semi-sweet-chocolate-chips tag-sugar tag-unbleached-all-purpose-flour tag-unsalted-butter tag-whole-wheat-pie-crust">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/chocolate-chip-cookie-dough-pie" title="Permalink to Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Pie" rel="bookmark">Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Pie</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/chocolate-chip-cookie-dough-pie" title="3:28 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">March 24, 2011</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/author/caroline" title="View all posts by caroline">caroline</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8864.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3620" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8864" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8864.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>Talk about decadent!</p>
<p>This pie is the ultimate cookie dough treat. It&#8217;s warm, gooey and of course, chocolatey!</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8864.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8819.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3617" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8819" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8819.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>We enjoyed it warm with a scoop of vanilla frozen yogurt. Yum!</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8819.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8855.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3618" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8855" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8855.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8857.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3619" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8857" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8857.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8857.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8865.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3621" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8865" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8865.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8865.jpg"></a><a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8869.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3622" title="ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8869" src="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/ChocolateChipCookieDoughPie-8869.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Pie</strong></p>
<h6><em>adapted from <a href="http://www.thenaptimechef.com/2011/03/not-just-for-the-derby-pie-powernap-recipe/" target="_blank">The Naptime Chef</a></em></h6>
<p><em>Ingredients</em></p>
<ul>
<li>3/4 cup sugar</li>
<li>1/2 unbleached all purpose flour</li>
<li>2 eggs, beaten</li>
<li>1 stick unsalted butter, melted</li>
<li>2 tablespoons Bourbon</li>
<li>1 cup honey roasted peanuts (optional)</li>
<li>1/2 semi-sweet chocolate chips</li>
<li>1/2 cup chopped Reese&#8217;s peanut butter cups</li>
</ul>
<p><em>How-To</em></p>
<ol>
<li>Make your <a href="http://chocolateandcarrots.com/2011/03/whole-wheat-pie-crust" target="_blank">whole wheat pie crust</a>.</li>
<li>Once the pie crust has cooled, it&#8217;s time to make the filling.</li>
<li>Preheat the oven to 325°.</li>
<li>In a large bowl, mix the sugar and flour together.</li>
<li>Mix in the eggs, butter and Bourbon until smooth and creamy.</li>
<li>Stir in the chocolate chips, peanut butter cups, and optional peanuts.</li>
<li>Pour the batter into the pie crust.</li>
<li>Bake for 45-60 minutes or until the pie isn&#8217;t giggly any more.</li>
<li>Let cool for about 5 minutes and serve warm.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Servings: about 10-12</em></p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
